div.head:
TO
ROBERT GROVE Eſq;
Of Fernes in VViltſhire;
AND TO
Madam TRYPHENA
His Conſort.

div.p:
Weighty indeed are theſe Precepts;
great be the Duties required, and great
the Sins forbidden.

                  They Contemn the Supream King's Authority;
and deny him to be Lord
over their Tongue.

                  They Deny God's Propriety in them;
conſtructively ſaying, their Tongues
(and, therefore, their Whole Perſons)
are their own. The Clay is its own;
and what hath the Potter to do with
it? Helliſh Conceit!
